This paper deals with bibliometric indices and their relationships, which are relevant to the field of computer science. The paper does not focus on any specific subfield of computer science, but rather on a general topic that could be of interest to researchers in various subfields. Based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper discusses the impact of bibliometric indices on the evaluation of researchers and their work. Other possible sub-categories include cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these subfields may also be interested in bibliometric analysis and its applications.
